            "max_check_attempts": 5,
            "notes": "Lists the container images on a host and checks how old they are. Reports each image's repository tag, age and size, and alerts when an image is older than the configured thresholds, which is a sign that a rebuild or pull was missed. Images can be selected or excluded by name using regular expressions. For Docker, use the docker-image check instead. Requires root or sudo.",
